description.narrative:
The development and endorsement of the National Community Health Strategy has strengthened the enabling environment for community based primary health care, through creating platforms at the various levels of the system for coordination, capacity building and continued engagement with communities. Through continued support to equip and capacitate over 17,000 village health workers, an estimated 4.6 million people were reached by Village Health Workers across the 60 rural districts and with preventive and promotional health services.
